  "texts": [
    "Traditional on-premises infrastructure may struggle to handle this influx, leading to delays in anomaly detection and response.",
    "To address these challenges, telecom operators are increasingly looking toward techniques such as distributed computing and edge AI (Taleb et al. 2017).",
    "By distributing the processing load across multiple servers or leveraging edge computing, data can be analyzed closer to its source, reducing computational overhead and latency while improving real-time responsiveness.",
    "Another significant challenge is the quality of telecom data, which is often noisy and imbalanced.",
    "Anomalies in network traffic, such as fraudulent calls or security breaches, are typically rare compared to normal events."
  ],
